Fixed in my local version with simple if/else logic that uses dict.items() if no PY2:

```if props is not None:
        jprops = jpype.java.util.Properties()
        if PY2:
            for k, v in props.iteritems():
                jprops.put(k, v)
        else:
            for k, v in props.items():
                jprops.put(k, v)
```

I have some queries that are failing on dates before 1970 because of the following code in _to_date.
    d = datetime.datetime.strptime(str(java_val)[:10], "%Y-%m-%d")
    return d.strftime("%Y-%m-%d")
I am using the following fix:
    y, m, d = [int(x) for x in str(java_val)[:10].split('-')]
    return datetime.date(y, m, d)
